  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life Saving Information Through Radio In South Sudan By CRN</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since the beginning of the crisis in South Sudan, information distribution has been biased: accessing reliable sources and deliver accurate information has been challenging. People, who often rely on news delivered by radio, are often unaware of what happens around them and cannot take informed decisions on what to do in case of need.

The Catholic Radio Network will therefore work towards delivery of regular life saving information to South Sudanese through the CRN stations covered areas with the aim of improving the resilience of South Sudanese during humanitarian crises.

This will ensure community members within reach through its network will be made aware of basic information to help face humanitarian crises through dissemination of regular and accurate and practicable information.</narrative>
  </description>
